The article is a transcript of remarks given by Vice President Mike Pence at the National Air and Space Museum in Washington, D.C. He thanks Jim Bridenstine, the Administrator of NASA, and other members of Congress for their support of American leadership in space. He also discusses the legacy of the Apollo 11 mission and the commitment to renewing American leadership in space. Pence mentions the revival of the National Space Council and the goal of returning to the moon and eventually sending Americans to Mars. He highlights the progress made in advancing the President's vision for space exploration and the budget request sent to Capitol Hill. Pence concludes by expressing his gratitude to the museum and encourages the audience to enjoy the premiere of a film about the Apollo 11 mission.